						               													<description>IGB&amp;Oacute; is an abstract strategy board game that teaches sustainable thinking. IGB&amp;Oacute; translates to 'forest' in Yoruba.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To begin, each player gets 36 &amp;quot;seeds&amp;quot; and 4 &amp;quot;desert&amp;quot; pieces. The game starts by flipping the IGB&amp;Oacute; piece. If IGB&amp;Oacute; lands face-up then the youngest player starts. The IGB&amp;Oacute; piece can be used as a neutral seed by both players, but neither player can stack on top of it.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Next, players now take turns to place pieces on the board. Desert pieces prevent growth and can be used defensively/offensively during the game. The seed pieces are used to form IGB&amp;Oacute;s.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;An IGB&amp;Oacute; is formed in the following ways:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Plant 5 seeds in a row, the center seed becomes the IGB&amp;Oacute; trunk AND/OR:&amp;#10;Plant two intersecting rows of 3 seeds, the center seed becomes the IGB&amp;Oacute; trunk.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Methods of scoring a single IGBO:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The center of each shape gains another seed and becomes the stacked trunk of the IGB&amp;Oacute;. Once an IGB&amp;Oacute; is stacked and formed, the other seeds in the formation are turned over to signify that they have become roots. Players add more symmetric root branches to their IGB&amp;Oacute; to take it to be a Double, Triple and Quadruple IGB&amp;Oacute;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The scoring is simple and works as follows:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Single IGB&amp;Oacute; gives you 2 points &amp;#10;Double IGB&amp;Oacute; gives you 4 points &amp;#10;Triple IGB&amp;Oacute; gives you 8 points &amp;#10;Quadruple IGB&amp;Oacute; gives you 16 points&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Another strategic element is the wind. Seeds that are not &amp;quot;rooted&amp;quot; can be blown in the wind and travel a maximum of 5 spaces on the board moving horizontally and vertically. This can be used to disguise your strategy to your opponent. On your turn, you may either plant a new seed or move two existing seeds.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
